import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

# Pivot table
df_x = pd.pivot_table(dataset, index=''State'', columns=''CustomQuarter'', values=''Total_Loss'', aggfunc=''sum'')

# Create large figure and axes
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(25, 15))

# Backgrounds
fig.patch.set_facecolor(''#09124f'')       # Set figure background
fig.patch.set_alpha(0.01)                # 35% visible, 65% transparent

ax.set_facecolor(''#09124f'')              # Set plot background
ax.patch.set_alpha(0.01)                 # 35% visible


# Plot
df_x.plot(
    kind=''barh'',
    stacked=True,
    color=[''#118DFF'', ''#12239E'', ''#E66C37'', ''#6B007B'', ''#E044A7''][:len(df_x.columns)],
    ax=ax
)

# Labels and ticks
ax.set_xlabel(''Loss (in Millions ₹)'', fontsize=56, color=''white'',fontweight=''bold'')
ax.set_ylabel(''State'', fontsize=56, color=''white'', fontweight=''bold'')
ax.tick_params(axis=''x'', labelsize=45, colors=''white'')
ax.tick_params(axis=''y'', labelsize=45, colors=''white'')

# ✅ Make tick labels bold
ax.set_xticklabels([label.get_text() for label in ax.get_xticklabels()], fontsize=45, color=''white'', fontweight=''bold'')
ax.set_yticklabels([label.get_text() for label in ax.get_yticklabels()], fontsize=45, color=''white'', fontweight=''bold'')
plt.xticks(rotation=0)

# Format X-axis as ₹Millions
formatter = ticker.FuncFormatter(lambda x, _: f''{int(x / 1_000_000)}'')
ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(formatter)

# ✅ Proper Legend with visible box and white text
legend = ax.legend(
    title=''Quarter'',
    fontsize=20,
    title_fontsize=22,
    loc=''upper right'',
    bbox_to_anchor=(1, 1)
)
plt.setp(legend.get_texts(), color=''white'')
plt.setp(legend.get_title(), color=''white'')
legend.get_frame().set_facecolor(''#444444'')   # Optional dark box background
legend.get_frame().set_edgecolor(''white'')     # White border

# Final layout
plt.tight_layout(pad=3.0)
plt.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

# Preprocessing
dataset[''OrderDate''] = pd.to_datetime(dataset[''OrderDate''])
dataset[''Sales_Before_Discount''] = dataset[''ProductPrice''] * dataset[''Quantity'']
daily = dataset.groupby(''OrderDate'')[[''Sales_after_Discount'', ''Sales_Before_Discount'']].sum().sort_index()

# Create large styled figure
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(25, 15))

# ✅ Set dark transparent background
fig.patch.set_facecolor(''#09124f'')
fig.patch.set_alpha(0.01)

ax.set_facecolor(''#09124f'')
ax.patch.set_alpha(0.01)

# ✅ Plot the lines
daily.plot(ax=ax, linewidth=3)

# ✅ Axis titles
# ax.set_title("Sales vs Sales Before Discount", fontsize=50, color=''white'', fontweight=''bold'')
ax.set_xlabel("Date", fontsize=56, color=''white'', fontname=''Arial'', fontweight=''bold'')
ax.set_ylabel("Amount", fontsize=56, color=''white'', fontname=''Arial'', fontweight=''bold'')

# ✅ Ticks styling
ax.tick_params(axis=''x'', labelsize=36, colors=''white'')
ax.tick_params(axis=''y'', labelsize=45, colors=''white'')

# ✅ Format Y-axis: no decimals
# ✅ Format Y-axis in Millions
formatter = ticker.FuncFormatter(lambda x, _: f''{int(x / 1_000_000)}M'')
ax.yaxis.set_major_formatter(formatter)


# ✅ Format X-axis dates (auto-format and white)
ax.xaxis.set_tick_params(rotation=0)
ax.set_xticklabels([label.get_text() for label in ax.get_xticklabels()], fontsize=36, color=''white'', fontweight=''bold'')
ax.set_yticklabels([label.get_text() for label in ax.get_yticklabels()], fontsize=45, color=''white'', fontweight=''bold'')

# ✅ Legend
legend = ax.legend(
    title='''',
    fontsize=20,
    loc=''upper left''
)
plt.setp(legend.get_texts(), color=''white'')
legend.get_frame().set_facecolor(''#444444'')
legend.get_frame().set_edgecolor(''white'')


# ✅ Grid and layout
ax.grid(True, color=''white'', alpha=0.2)
plt.tight_layout(pad=3.0)
plt.show()
